                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 9.141,
                                "byte_start": 74522,
                                "byte_stop": 111093,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 89-1448 Virginia Bankshares versus Sandberg will be announced by Justice Souter."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.141,
                        "stop": 242.808,
                        "byte_start": 111093,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15042,
                            "name": "David H. Souter",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/david_h_souter",
                            "last_name": "Souter",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2686,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 655362000,
                                    "date_end": 1246251600,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2686"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32703,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 42141,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/david_souter.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 6839,
                            "identifier": "david_h_souter"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.141,
                                "stop": 15.036,
                                "byte_start": 111093,
                                "byte_stop": 134708,
                                "text": "This case comes to us by writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Fourth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.036,
                                "stop": 34.882,
                                "byte_start": 134708,
                                "byte_stop": 214120,
                                "text": "The directors of the First American Bank of Virginia approved to proposal for a freeze-out merger under which its minority shareholders will be paid $42 a share for their stock by a holding company, Virginia Bankshares Incorporated, following which, the minority shareholders would loose their interest in the bank."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 34.882,
                                "stop": 41.48,
                                "byte_start": 214120,
                                "byte_stop": 240452,
                                "text": "Although the holding company owned enough First American stock to approve the merger without the votes of the minority shareholders."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 41.48,
                                "stop": 59.081,
                                "byte_start": 240452,
                                "byte_stop": 310878,
                                "text": "First American\u2019s directors, nonetheless, circulated a proxy solicitation to the minority shareholders in which the directors urged support for the merger and stated that they had approved the plan because it provided an opportunity for the minority shareholders to receive a high value for their stock."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 59.081,
                                "stop": 84.705,
                                "byte_start": 310878,
                                "byte_stop": 413382,
                                "text": "After the merger, the respondent, Dora Sandberg a former minority shareholder of the bank, brought suit against the holding companies and the directors of the bank for soliciting proxies by means of materially false or misleading statements in violation of Section 14(a) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 and the Securities and Exchange Commission rule 14(a)(9)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 84.705,
                                "stop": 98.339,
                                "byte_start": 413382,
                                "byte_stop": 467926,
                                "text": "Sandberg argued that the statement by the directors, that they had approved the merger because minority shareholders would receive a high value for their shares was false and that even though her vote was not necessary to authorize the merger."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 98.339,
                                "stop": 111.79,
                                "byte_start": 467926,
                                "byte_stop": 521738,
                                "text": "She should be permitted to bring a private action for damages under Section 14(a) because the proxy solicitation had for other reasons formed a link in the chain of causation ultimately resulting in damage to her."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 111.79,
                                "stop": 116.107,
                                "byte_start": 521738,
                                "byte_stop": 538979,
                                "text": "Her suit was successful in the District Court, and the Court of Appeals affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 116.107,
                                "stop": 132.358,
                                "byte_start": 538979,
                                "byte_stop": 603972,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the Clerk today, we hold the directors\u2019 statement actionable under Section 14(a), but we hold further that Sandberg has not satisfied her burden to demonstrate causation between the proxy solicitation in her damages and we accordingly reverse the lower court\u2019s judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 132.358,
                                "stop": 145.308,
                                "byte_start": 603972,
                                "byte_stop": 655799,
                                "text": "A knowingly false statement of reasons, opinions, and beliefs by a corporate director contained in a proxy solicitation maybe actionable under rule 14(a)(9), that is because it satisfies two conditions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 145.308,
                                "stop": 150.097,
                                "byte_start": 655799,
                                "byte_stop": 674920,
                                "text": "First, the reasonable shareholder would consider it important in deciding how to vote."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 150.097,
                                "stop": 164.464,
                                "byte_start": 674920,
                                "byte_stop": 732390,
                                "text": "Second, such statement is subject to proof or disproof as a factual assertion that the directors\u2019 act for the reason that was given or hold to belief statement, and the independent facts justify acting for such reasons or holding such a belief."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 164.464,
                                "stop": 180.221,
                                "byte_start": 732390,
                                "byte_stop": 795502,
                                "text": "In this case, for example, Sandberg and others presented evidence about the bank\u2019s assets and its actual and potential level of operation to prove with the directors\u2019 statement was misleading about the stock\u2019s value and a false explanation of the directors\u2019 reasons for approving the merger."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 180.221,
                                "stop": 186.317,
                                "byte_start": 795502,
                                "byte_stop": 819848,
                                "text": "We, nonetheless, reverse the judgment because we hold that Sandberg has not demonstrated causation of damages."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 186.317,
                                "stop": 200.977,
                                "byte_start": 819848,
                                "byte_stop": 878466,
                                "text": "One theory of causation she advances is that the proxy statement was a means of obtaining minority approval without which the parties to the merger would have been unwilling to proceed regardless of the fact that minority approval was not legally required."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 200.977,
                                "stop": 208.985,
                                "byte_start": 878466,
                                "byte_stop": 910545,
                                "text": "We reject this theory because it would predicate liability on speculation about the state of mind of corporate directors in a hypothetical situation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 208.985,
                                "stop": 224.725,
                                "byte_start": 910545,
                                "byte_stop": 973448,
                                "text": "We reject respondent\u2019s further theory of causation that the proxy statement was used to obtain votes of the minority shareholders that bar the subsequent action in State Court to avoid the merger because there was no showing that such a state law remedy is no longer available."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 224.725,
                                "stop": 229.37,
                                "byte_start": 973448,
                                "byte_stop": 992047,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has filed an opinion concurring in part and concurring in the judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 229.37,
                                "stop": 235.458,
                                "byte_start": 992047,
                                "byte_stop": 1016393,
                                "text": "Justice Stevens has filed an opinion concurring in part and dissenting in part in which Justice Marshall has joined."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 235.458,
                                "stop": 242.808,
                                "byte_start": 1016393,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Kennedy has filed an opinion concurring in part and dissenting in part in which Justices Marshall, Blackmun, and Stevens have joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
